{"id":1273,"date":"2022-02-27T16:16:00","date_gmt":"2022-02-27T16:16:00","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/?p=1273"},"modified":"2022-02-23T10:19:44","modified_gmt":"2022-02-23T10:19:44","slug":"configure-superuser-access","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/?p=1273","title":{"rendered":"Configure superuser access"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>In Linux and Unix like computer operating systems, root is the conventional name of the user who has all rights or permissions (to all files and programs) in all modes (single- or multi-user).<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Become a superuser in Linux using sudo and su<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"is-layout-flow wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<pre class=\"wp-block-preformatted\">sudo -i<\/pre>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can also use su(switch user)\u00a0command with sudo\u00a0to switch your user. If you are currently logged in as non-root user then you can use\u00a0<code>sudo su -<\/code>\u00a0command to login as\u00a0<code>root<\/code>\u00a0user as specified below<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"is-layout-flow wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<pre class=\"wp-block-preformatted\">sudo su -<\/pre>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Adding a superuser access to a specific user\/group<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>On\u00a0Unix-like\u00a0operating systems, the\u00a0<strong>visudo<\/strong>\u00a0command edits the\u00a0<strong>sudoers<\/strong>\u00a0file, which is used by the\u00a0<strong>sudo<\/strong>\u00a0command. To change what users and groups are allowed to run\u00a0<strong>sudo<\/strong>, run\u00a0<strong>visudo<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"640\" height=\"63\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-195.png?resize=640%2C63&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1301\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-195.png?w=849&amp;ssl=1 849w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-195.png?resize=300%2C29&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-195.png?resize=768%2C75&amp;ssl=1 768w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-195.png?resize=24%2C2&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-195.png?resize=36%2C4&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-195.png?resize=48%2C5&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"632\" height=\"70\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-196.png?resize=632%2C70&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1302\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-196.png?w=632&amp;ssl=1 632w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-196.png?resize=300%2C33&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-196.png?resize=24%2C3&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-196.png?resize=36%2C4&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-196.png?resize=48%2C5&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 632px) 100vw, 632px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h3>Using a wheel group<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Rather than have to dole out individual permissions on a system, you can add users to the wheel group and they can gain access to administrator levels, simply by being in the wheel group. It&#8217;s typically tied directly into\u00a0<code>sudo<\/code>.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"is-layout-flow wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>## Allows people in group wheel to run all commands\n%wheel  ALL=(ALL)   ALL\n<\/code><\/pre>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Which means you can do anything on the system with\u00a0<code>sudo &lt;cmd><\/code>.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Adding user do the wheel group<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"is-layout-flow wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<pre class=\"wp-block-preformatted\"><strong>usermod -aG <\/strong>wheel user_name<\/pre>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"481\" height=\"21\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-197.png?resize=481%2C21&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1303\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-197.png?w=481&amp;ssl=1 481w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-197.png?resize=300%2C13&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-197.png?resize=24%2C1&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-197.png?resize=36%2C2&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/image-197.png?resize=48%2C2&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 481px) 100vw, 481px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>In Linux and Unix like computer operating systems, root is the conventional name of the [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":1305,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"stand